{
  "texts": [
    "For example, LLM4DyG [115] examines that providing only one example can significantly improve the accuracy of LLM on multiple dynamic graph tasks such as \"when link\", \"when connect\", \"when triadic closure\", \"neighbor at time\" and \"neighbor in periods\".",
    "On the other hand, LLM can perform reasoning in a given context and solve dynamic graph related tasks.",
    "This insight motivates new applications of LLMs in dynamic graph learning tasks and potentially transforms approaches in related fields.",
    "Although LLMs have demonstrated inspiring understanding capabilities on dynamic graph tasks, they still face challenges as follows.• Processing large-scale graphs.",
    "As graph size grows, the performance of LLMs markedly declines [116]."
  ]
}